"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612647\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612647\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dqm1665702642634.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dqm1665702642634.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dqm1665702642634.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dqm1665702642634\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                              \n Use Extended Triggers\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determines whether widget triggers (also known as extended triggers) can be fired by the widget. The default value depends on the widget. <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__p_d108752e1_d108753e1_d108754e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>ExtendedTriggers<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> |\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__table_d12806e1_d12807e1_d12808e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__table_d12806e1_d12807e1_d12808e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__table_d12806e1_d12807e1_d12808e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dqm1665702642634__table_d12806e1_d12807e1_d12808e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dqm1665702642634__table_d12806e1_d12807e1_d12808e1__entry__2\">The widget can execute extended triggers. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dqm1665702642634__table_d12806e1_d12807e1_d12808e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dqm1665702642634__table_d12806e1_d12807e1_d12808e1__entry__2\">The widget cannot execute extended triggers. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__section_hyj_1q5_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449652e126\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__table_d12809e1_d12810e1_d12811e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dynamic? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Depends on widget </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported in Grid? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> No </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dependencies: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Applies to: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"klb1688454363706.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/klb1688454363706.html\" title=\"Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report.\">EditBox</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ied1665702642247.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ied1665702642247.html\" title=\"The uhtml widget is a field-level widget in a form component that renders HTML code (including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) or displays a web page (when the field value is a URL prefixed by an ampersand (&amp;www.mysite.com/doc/index.html). Uniface provides a logical widget called HTML, which is mapped to uhtml.\">uhtml (HTML Widget)</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vvo1665702647716.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vvo1665702647716.html\" title=\"The uOcxContainer widget embeds a Microsoft OCX control into a form component, and maps OCX properties and OCX events to fields and triggers. You can use ProcScript to activate OCX methods and let the OCX control activate widget triggers to respond to OCX events.\">uOcxContainer (OcxContainer)</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__section_fb4_cq5_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449652e214\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__p_d108761e1_d108762e1_d108763e1\">Calls to extended triggers are asynchronous, so you\n            can not have OUT parameters or return values.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__section_rpt_dq5_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449652e223\">OCX Container</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__p_d108767e1_d108768e1_d108769e1\">For the OCX Container widget, this is a static\n            property. It cannot be set in ProcScript. The available widget triggers depend on the\n            OCX Control that is loaded in the container. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"edd1665702649050.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/edd1665702649050.html\" title=\"The OCX container widget does not have a fixed set of interactive triggers because each OCX has its own set of events. You can implement widget triggers (previously known as extended triggers) to respond to these events.\">Interactive Widget Triggers for OCX Controls</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__section_swg_fq5_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449652e243\">HTML Widget</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__p_d108773e1_d108774e1_d108775e1\">For the HTML Widget, this property is dynamic; by\n            default it is <code class=\"ph codeph\">true</code>. Unlike other widgets, the HTML widget has no\n            pre-defined widget triggers; you are entirely free to define your own triggers.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__p_d108776e1_d108777e1_d108778e1\">These widget triggers can be called by JavaScript\n            in the HTML widget, as long as the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Enable JavaScript</span> widget\n            property is <code class=\"ph codeph\">true</code>. In this case, a JavaScript object named\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">unifaceTriggers</code> is created and bound to <code class=\"ph codeph\">window</code>\n            object.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__note_yjt_hq5_1xb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Calls to widget triggers are asynchronous, so you\n            cannot define extended triggers with OUT or INOUT parameters, or return values.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__section_u2y_hq5_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449652e273\">Example: Calling Extended Trigger of HTML Widget</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__p_d108782e1_d108783e1_d108784e1\">For example, you can call the extended trigger\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">func1</code> with two parameters <code class=\"ph codeph\">param1</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">param2</code>, as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__pre_hdt_jq5_1xb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">&lt;script language=\"javascript\"&gt;\nwindow.unifaceTriggers('func1,'param1', 'param2');\n&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__section_hg5_lq5_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449652e294\">Using in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__p_d108788e1_d108789e1_d108790e1\">For the HTML widget, you can use\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$properties</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldproperties</span> to set or get\n            the ExtendedTriggers property and its value. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zie1665702558978.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zie1665702558978.html\" title=\"Return or set the current widget properties of a field.\">$properties</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aud1705998763272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1705998763272.html\" title=\"Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field.\">$fieldproperties</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"dqm1665702642634__pre_og4_mq5_1xb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$fieldproperties(FLD) = \"ExtendedTriggers=False\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gaj1665702642705.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Enable JavaScript</a><p>Determines whether JavaScript is allowed to be executed in the widget. True (default) or False.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612647\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612647\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Use Extended Triggers Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Use Extended Triggers Determines whether widget triggers (also known as extended triggers) can be fired by the widget. The default value depends on the widget. True or False \" ExtendedTriggers = True | False \" Value Description True The widget can execute extended triggers. False The widget cannot execute extended triggers. Usage Dynamic? Depends on widget Supported in Grid? No Dependencies: None Applies to: EditBox uhtml (HTML Widget) uOcxContainer (OcxContainer) Description Calls to extended triggers are asynchronous, so you can not have OUT parameters or return values. OCX Container For the OCX Container widget, this is a static property. It cannot be set in ProcScript. The available widget triggers depend on the OCX Control that is loaded in the container. For more information, see Interactive Widget Triggers for OCX Controls . HTML Widget For the HTML Widget, this property is dynamic; by default it is true . Unlike other widgets, the HTML widget has no pre-defined widget triggers; you are entirely free to define your own triggers. These widget triggers can be called by JavaScript in the HTML widget, as long as the Enable JavaScript widget property is true . In this case, a JavaScript object named unifaceTriggers is created and bound to window object. Note: Calls to widget triggers are asynchronous, so you cannot define extended triggers with OUT or INOUT parameters, or return values. Example: Calling Extended Trigger of HTML Widget For example, you can call the extended trigger func1 with two parameters param1 and param2 , as follows: <script language=\"javascript\"> window.unifaceTriggers('func1,'param1', 'param2'); </script> Copy Using in ProcScript For the HTML widget, you can use $properties or $fieldproperties to set or get the ExtendedTriggers property and its value. For more information, see $properties and $fieldproperties . $fieldproperties(FLD) = \"ExtendedTriggers=False\" Copy Related Links Enable JavaScript Determines whether JavaScript is allowed to be executed in the widget. True (default) or False. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}